OL,3,GGrampian
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FThe morning will be dry and
OL,6,Flargely cloudy, but with some bright
OL,7,Fspells along the north coast. Rain
OL,8,Fwill spread east in the afternoon.
OL,9,FMild.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FIt will be cloudy through the
OL,12,Fevening with rain slowly spreading
OL,13,Feast, Rain turning to snow on the
OL,14,Fhills before clearing overnight, which
OL,15,Fmay allow some frost to develop.
OL,16,
OL,17,CFriday:FA cold and quite cloudy start
OL,18,Fwith some frost. Then a dry and
OL,19,Fincreasingly sunny day, but feeling
OL,20,Fcooler than recent days.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
